The Bruneian invasion of Palawan, was a military invasion of Kedatuan of Taytay in Palawan by the Bruneian Sultanate and the Sultanate of Sulu in the 15th century. The invasion resulted in the annexation of central and southern Palawan.
Background
In , prior to the Spanish reached in the Philippines, the Bruneian Empire, launched an attack on the Kedatuan of Taytay.
